         <abstract>
            <p>We prove a six-parameter identity whose terms have the form x&lt;sup&gt;α&lt;/sup&gt; T(k&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;, l&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;)T(k&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;, l&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;), where T(k, l) = ∑&lt;sup&gt;∞&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;-∞&lt;/sub&gt; x&lt;sup&gt;kn&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; + ln&lt;/sup&gt;. This identity is then used to give a new proof of the familiar Ramanujan identity H(x)G(x&lt;sup&gt;11&lt;/sup&gt;) - x&lt;sup&gt;2G&lt;/sup&gt;(x)H(x&lt;sup&gt;11&lt;/sup&gt;) = 1, where &lt;tex-math&gt;$G(x) = \prod^\infty_{n = 0} \lbrack (1 - x^{5n + 1})(1 - x^{5n + 4})\rbrack^{-1}$&lt;/tex-math&gt; and &lt;tex-math&gt;$H(x) = \prod^\infty_{n = 0}\lbrack(1 - x^{5n + 2})(1 - x^{5n + 3})\rbrack^{-1}$&lt;/tex-math&gt;. Two other identities, called "balanced Q&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; identities", are also established through its use.</p>
          </abstract>
